<section class="container help-page">
    <div class="list-group">
        <div  class="list-group-item list-group-item-action " aria-current="true">
          <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">
            <h5 class="mb-1">1.)Why is the page stuck on loading when i searched something?</h5>

          </div>
          <p class="mb-1">It's probably because the character you entered is too small. For example, if you searched 'dra' instead of 'dragon , you might get stuck in the loading loop, better refresh the page.'</p>
          <small>Or it can be something wrong with the backend data</small>
        </div>
        <div class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
          <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">
            <h5 class="mb-1">2.)Why are there popus and weird ads on the episode page?</h5>
 
          </div>
          <p class="mb-1">Because i'm not the one hosting those video streams, i'm just using gogoanime's data.</p>

        </div>
        <div class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
          <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">
            <h5 class="mb-1">3.)Why is the search page empty?</h5>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-1">It is because the anime you are searching isn't available or has broken links.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
            <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">
              <h5 class="mb-1">3.)Why is the anime list page empty?</h5>
            </div>
            <p class="mb-1">It is because you tried to access a page number that doesn't exist.How to sort according to alphabets and which page number to jump to, are all written on that page too!</p>
          </div>
          <div class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
            <div class="d-flex w-100 justify-content-between">
              <h5 class="mb-1">3.)Why does it take too long to load a page or why does it take long to navigate to other pages?</h5>
            </div>
            <p class="mb-1">The answer is simple, i'm using a free account of heroku(The platform where i deployed the app) , there are multiple limitations on the free account like only one person can access the page at one time ,the app will switch to sleep mode if it isn't visited much etc.And then there's another reason for long loading time which is sloppy coding, i'm not the best at web development and this is my 3rd project ,so it is what it is!</p>
          </div>
      </div>

